    Fits outcome model

    getModel.Rd

    Fits outcome model

    getModel(
  d,
  exposure,
  exposure_time_pts,
  outcome,
  epochs,
  exp_epochs,
  int_order,
  model,
  fam,
  covariates,
  verbose
)

    Arguments

    d

    wide data frame

    exposure

    name of exposure variable

    exposure_time_pts

    list of integers at which weights will be created/assessed that correspond to time points when exposure was measured

    outcome

    name of outcome variable with ".timepoint" suffix

    epochs

    data frame of exposure epoch labels and values

    exp_epochs

    list of exposure epochs

    int_order

    integer specification of highest order exposure main effects interaction for interaction models

    model

    character indicating one of the following outcome models:

    • "m0" (exposure main effects)

    • "m1" (exposure main effects & covariates)

    • "m2" (exposure main effects & their interactions)

    • "m3" (exposure main effects, their interactions, & covariates)

    • "covs" (covariate only model)

    • "int" (intercept only model)

    fam

    function specification for svyglm model

    covariates

    list of characters reflecting variable names of covariates for covariate models

    verbose

    TRUE or FALSE indicator for user output (default is TRUE)

    Value

    list of fitted model(s)

    Examples

    test <- data.frame(ID = 1:50,
                   A.1 = rnorm(n = 50),
                   A.2 = rnorm(n = 50),
                   A.3 = rnorm(n = 50),

                   B.2 = rnorm(n = 50),
                   B.3 = rnorm(n = 50),
                   C = rnorm(n = 50),
                   D.3 = rnorm(n = 50))
test[, c("A.1", "A.2", "A.3")] <- lapply(test[, c("A.1", "A.2", "A.3")], as.numeric)

                    ti_confounders = "C",
